<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1926-09-17T14:45:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1926-09-17T14:45:00-05:00" n="491" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d491">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/3803: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dennis</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1926-09-17T14:00:00-05:45"><hi rend="italic">September 17,
                                        1926—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 10:23
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>137. Please advise immediately whether United States will, as requested
                            in writing by Chamorro, have neutral zone around wharf and hotel
                            maintained by marines at Corinto for conference. This is necessary as
                            lodging and meeting facilities of warship not adequate.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dennis</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>